managements discussion and analysis  jpmorgan chase & co.   dealer/client business  at december31, 2007, the total notional amount of protection
purchased and sold in the dealer/client business increased $3.3 trillion from year-end 2006 as a result of increased trade volume in the market. the risk positions are largely matched when securities used to risk-manage certain derivative positions
are taken into consideration and the notional amounts are adjusted to a duration-based equivalent or to reflect different degrees of subordination in tranched structures.  credit portfolio activities  in managing its wholesale credit exposure, the firm purchases single-name and portfolio credit derivatives; this activity
does not reduce the reported level of assets on the balance sheet or the level of reported offbalance sheet commitments. the firm also diversifies its exposures by providing (i.e., selling) credit protection, which increases exposure to
industries or clients where the firm has little or no client-related exposure. this activity is not material to the firms overall credit exposure.  use of
