assumptions to the change in fair value may not be linear. also, in the table, the effect that a change in  a particular assumption may have on the fair value is calculated without changing any other assumption. in reality, changes in one factor may result in changes in another, which
might counteract or magnify the sensitivities.   expected static-pool net
